    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi,\n\nmy machine is a 6.19.14-400.asahi.fc44.aarch64+16k. (Apple M1 Silicon)\nzig version is 0.16.0.\n\nBuilding target `aarch64-linux` **fails** on my aarch64 machine.\nBuilding target `x86_64-linux ` succeeds on my aarch64 machine.\n\nBuilding target `aarch64-linux` succeeds on another x86_64 machine (deb13, same zig version).\nBuilding target `x86_64-linux ` succeeds on another x86_64 machine.\n\nI think the last time I built neovim with zig was in Febuary 2026. (Did not tried since)\n\nThe Log:\n```log\nnvim_dev\n+- install generated/\n   +- WriteFile syntax/vim/generated.vim\n      +- run exe nlua0 (generated.vim)\n         +- run exe nlua0 (funcs.generated.h)\n            +- run exe nlua0 (api/private/dispatch_wrappers.generated.h)\n               +- run exe nlua0 (api/extmark.c.generated.h) failure\nerror: OutOfMemory\n/opt/src/neovim/zig-pkg/zlua-0.1.0-hGRpC22ABQA4y12Uz7QaHuCkKrpaa_66xidApjtFuKFg/src/lib.zig:768:16: 0x126428b in init (nlua0)\n        } else return error.OutOfMemory;\n               ^\n/opt/src/neovim/src/nlua0.zig:27:15: 0x1160cbb in init_lua (nlua0)\n    var lua = try Lua.init(std.heap.c_allocator);\n              ^\n/opt/src/neovim/src/nlua0.zig:75:17: 0x1161347 in main (nlua0)\n    const lua = try init_lua();\n                ^\nerror: process exited with error \n***snipped, log has in summary 8927 lines***\n```\n\nThe Error message is missleading, I'm not running out of memory, there is a problem in the switch of a null value: \n\n```zig\n/// This function is defined in luau.cpp and must be called to define the assertion printer\nextern \"c\" fn zig_registerAssertionHandler() void;\n\n```\n\n```zig\n    pub fn init(a: Allocator) error{OutOfMemory}!*Lua {\n        if (lang == .luau) zig_registerAssertionHandler();\n\n        // the userdata passed to alloc needs to be a pointer with a consistent address\n        // so we allocate an Allocator struct to hold a copy of the allocator's data\n        const allocator_ptr = try a.create(Allocator);\n        allocator_ptr.* = a;\n\n        if (switch (lang) {\n            .lua55 => c.lua_newstate(alloc, allocator_ptr, 0),\n            else => c.lua_newstate(alloc, allocator_ptr),\n        }) |state| {\n            return @ptrCast(state);\n        } else return error.OutOfMemory;\n    }\n```\n\nI know this is a third party dependency, but I saw that @bfredl is also involved in this repository. Maybe he can give some insights.\nThe problem is, that this is only repoducable on an aarch64 builder machine. Other zig projects are building fine. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\n# clean up deps and caches before building\nmake clean distclean\nrm -rf zig-pkg\nzig build -Dtarget=aarch64-linux\n\n# clean up deps and caches before building\nmake clean distclean\nrm -rf zig-pkg\nzig build -Dtarget=x86_64-linux\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nshould build\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nlatest\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.19.14-400.asahi.fc44.aarch64+16k\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n-\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n-\n\n### Installation\n\nrepo",
