            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The code is a bit hard to read but I don't think it is misleading, what happened was that `c.lua_newstate()` returned a `null` value which is only supposed to happen on OutOfMemory (which just means that the system/libc refused the process a mallocation somewhere, not necessarily that the system is hosed as a whole)\n\nit is a bit of a hack, but you can try `zig build -Dhost=native` on your AAarch64 machine. what happens then will actually use lua5.1 to run `nlua0` at build time but still link with luajit for the final executable. \n",
